---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="DIS Workshop 2025: From Dead-Ends to Dialogue: Third Workshop on GenAI & Design Research" 
  description="Join us at DIS 2025 in Portugal to explore and overcome stopsigns in GenAI and Design Research through collaborative analysis and hands-on activities."
  ogImage="https://willemvandermaden.com/square-workshop.png"
>
  <section class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-6">
    <figure>
      <img src="/header-workshop.png" alt="Workshop Header Image" class="w-full rounded-lg mb-1" />
      <figcaption class="text-xs text-gray-400 text-right mb-4">Image generated by Imagen 3, prompted by Willem van der Maden</figcaption>
    </figure>
    
    <h1 class="font-bold text-3xl">From Dead-Ends to Dialogue: Third Workshop on GenAI & Design Research</h1>
    
    <p class="opacity-60">
      DIS '25 Companion, July 5–9, 2025, Funchal, Portugal
    </p>
    
    <p>
      This workshop focuses on 'stopsigns'—the blockages that impede progress in design research with GenAI. These manifest as both semantic barriers (political, social, or mental frameworks) and pragmatic hurdles (technical limitations or implementation challenges). Through analysis of real cases and hands-on activities, we'll develop strategies for moving beyond these obstacles while acknowledging their legitimate concerns. Our goal is to foster more thoughtful integration of GenAI in design research and practice.
    </p>
    
    <p class="font-medium text-blue-400">
      We warmly welcome returning participants from our previous workshops, as well as newcomers looking to join this growing community of GenAI design researchers. The diverse mix of experiences enriches our collective exploration of this rapidly evolving field.
    </p>
    
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Key Dates</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 opacity-80">
        <li>Submission Deadline: <s>13th June 2025</s> <strong>23rd June 2025</strong><br/><span class="text-xs text-blue-400">Early submitters have already received an email; extension open for a few more spots!</span></li>
        <li>Notification of Acceptance: <s>20th June 2025</s> <strong>27th June 2025</strong></li>
        <li>Workshop Date: 6th July 2025</li>
        <li><em>Note: For those who need notification before the early bird registration deadline, please request this via email before June 3rd.</em></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Call for Participation</h2>
      <p class="opacity-80">
        Generative artificial intelligence (GenAI) dominates contemporary discourse—it's the zeitgeist, the perpetual headline, the topic that's transformed every coffee break into an impromptu tech summit. Yet while theoretical discussions abound, design researchers often get stuck on both "semantic stopsigns"—oversimplified narratives that halt deeper inquiry—and practical barriers that stall real-world progress. From blanket rejections to implementation hurdles, these challenges prevent thoughtful integration of GenAI in design research.
      </p>
      <a href="/DISworkshop2025/submissions" class="text-blue-500 underline">Read more →</a>
    </div>
    
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <a href="/DISworkshop2025/agenda" class="underline underline-offset-4 opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity w-fit">View the Agenda →</a>
      <a href="/DISworkshop2025/submissions" class="underline underline-offset-4 opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity w-fit">Submit Your Paper →</a>
      <a href="/DISworkshop2025/organizers" class="underline underline-offset-4 opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity w-fit">Meet the Organizers →</a>
      <a href="/DISworkshop2025/info" class="underline underline-offset-4 opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity w-fit">More Information →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>